------------------------------------------
  The initial vendoring pass was NOT gap-free: one real upstream file,
  `vm2/security/audit/vm2-context-injection.yaml`, was missed on the first
  copy — its paired `.js` fixture had been vendored but the rule definition
  itself was left orphaned. This was caught in review, the file was re-fetched
  from the same pinned commit (verified against the git-tree listing, not
  fabricated), and added. The count below reflects the corrected total.
  Earlier wording claiming the vendor set was fully verified against the
  git-tree with zero gaps was inaccurate and has been removed.

